cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the recognition of surgical phases in laparoscopic videos, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes the use of deep architectures and temporal constraints, which are common in robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging (cs.MM) as it focuses on laparoscopic videos of cholecystectomy procedures.
